-- Tiger Global Fourth-Biggest Groupon Holder After Shares
-- B y   K a t h e r i n e   B u r t o n
-- 2013-02-14T23:45:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-14/tiger-global-fourth-biggest-groupon-holder-after-shares.html
Tiger Global Management LLC, the
hedge fund founded by  Chase Coleman , become the fourth-largest
holder of Groupon Inc. after adding 63.7 million shares in the
last quarter, according to a regulatory filing today.  Tiger Global holds 9.95 percent of the shares, a position
valued at $316 million at the end of the year, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg.  Groupon  shares  have surged 12 percent in the past two days
amid optimism that its new e-commerce service may expand to more
cities, bolstering sales. The operator of the largest daily-
deals website has tumbled 70 percent since its November 2011
initial public offering.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katherine Burton in New York at 
